descript.abstract: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer. Geometry and attribute information updated Jan 2018.

horizpa.horizpar: Data compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy over the MassGIS color orthos from 2008/2009; these orthos are known to be +/- 10' horizontal; however, this data set cannot be used to reach authoritative conclusions about the horizontal accuracy of the boundaries depicted. That work requires a licensed land surveyor.

srcinfo.typesrc: Shapefiles and tif's of paper tax maps
srcinfo.srccontr: This GIS dataset represents a digital version of assessor tax maps that were previously converted and processed to be compliant with MassGIS Level 2 parcel standards, and now provides the basic framework for the upgrade to level 3.

procstep.procdesc: Existing digital data and tax maps fit to an orthophoto base. Parcel lines were modified to fit ground features in some instances. Quality checks applied, such as topology checks for gaps, overlaps for features in the newly created digital dataset. Relationship between the parcel fabric and assessor table performed. Any discrepancies were delivered to the assessor.

overview.dsoverv: M127TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Hatfield that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M127Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M127OthLeg and M127Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
